    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think we should always have the data about the latency, that is exposed by the timers, but if the comment says that collecting stats has a non negligible side effect on performance, then I am afraid that these stats could not be useful at all, because they could modify the behaviour of Besu. cc: @ahamlat on which is a tollerable overhead for collecting metrics.\r\n\r\nAt this point I am thinking that a refactor could be required to reduce the overhead of these metrics collection, another option is to leverage the stats that RocksDB dump on its logs at regular intervals, that as last resort could be also delegated to an external process.\r\n",
